  "description": {
    "en": "Gray wolves are highly social apex predators that live and hunt in family groups called packs.",
    "zh": "灰狼是高度社会化的顶级掠食者，以被称为「狼群」的家族群体生活和狩猎。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "Gray wolves are the largest wild members of the dog family, weighing 30 to 80 kilograms. They have powerful jaws, long legs built for running, and thick fur that can be gray, black, white, or brown. Their large paws act like snowshoes, helping them walk on top of deep snow.",
      "zh": "灰狼是犬科中体型最大的野生成员，体重30到80公斤。它们有强有力的下颌、适合奔跑的长腿和厚厚的毛皮，毛色可以是灰色、黑色、白色或棕色。它们的大脚掌就像雪鞋一样，帮助它们在深雪上行走。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "Wolves live in packs of 5 to 10 members led by a breeding pair. They hunt together to take down large prey like elk and deer, using teamwork and clever strategies. Wolves communicate with each other through howling, body language, and scent marking, and their howls can be heard up to 16 kilometers away.",
      "zh": "狼群通常由5到10个成员组成，由一对繁殖配偶领导。它们协同狩猎，用团队合作和聪明的策略捕捉麋鹿和鹿等大型猎物。狼通过嚎叫、身体语言和气味标记来相互交流，它们的嚎叫声最远可以传到16公里之外。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "Gray wolves once roamed across most of North America, Europe, and Asia. Today they live in tundra, forests, mountains, and grasslands in remote areas. In the United States, they are found mainly in Alaska, the northern Rocky Mountains, and the Great Lakes region.",
      "zh": "灰狼曾经在北美洲、欧洲和亚洲的大部分地区漫游。如今它们生活在偏远地区的苔原、森林、山脉和草原上。在美国，它们主要分布在阿拉斯加、北落基山脉和五大湖地区。"
    }
  },
